Reasoning: The paper discusses a modified online learning algorithm that uses second-order methods as Newton steps to handle large multi-class datasets. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), computer vision (cs.CV), and computational linguistics (cs.CL). However, since the focus is on online learning and regret bounds, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories. The use of element-wise multiplication is also relevant to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and computer vision (cs.CV), where matrix operations are common. Finally, the mention of mistake rates suggests that the paper may also be relevant to natural language processing (cs.CL), where classification and error analysis are important topics.
